Four persons have reportedly died while eight others sustained injuries in an accident on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. The crash, which involved a trailer and a Mazda bus, occurred on Saturday night at Foursquare in Ogunmakin. Democracy Day: Nigerians seek more dividends Terrorists killed 55 iron mongers in Borno in 3wks â€“ Police The Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in Ogun State, Ahmed Umar, confirmed the incident to newsmen. According to him, the accident occurred at 9 pm and was caused by excessive speed and loss of control on the part of the bus driver who rammed into the stationary truck. Umar explained that 13 people were involved in the accident which comprised 12 men and one woman, saying eight people got injured while four persons died comprising three men and a woman.